        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "Added a country column in the message list.  This will show the country of the sender from the MailHops API."
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/mailhops/versions/3.2.0",
        "version": "3.2.0"
    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "Using the MailHops API from <a href=\"https://www.MailHops.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.MailHops.com</a> this Add-on will show the location of the sender.  From there you can click on the location and view a map of the IP hops that a message took to get to your inbox.  Distance is also calculated to give you the miles or kilometers that a message traveled.  It will also show the senders weather if you add a DarkSky API key.  User agent, DKIM and other Authentication used by the sender.  Filter by country origin, mark as junk if the message took too long or is from a country you don't trust."
    },
